Media is reporting that the young men were arrested in Zaria while attending a party organised for two men who tied the knot. JOHANNESBURG Police have arrested 53 young men who celebrated a gay wedding on charges of &quot;belonging to a gang of unlawful society&quot;.The Associated Press is reporting that the young men were arrested on Saturday in the northern city of Zaria while attending a party organised for two men who tied the knot last week.While Nigerian law bans gay marriage, some couples conduct informal ceremonies.The 53 men pleaded not guilty to charges that also included conspiracy and unlawful assembly.They'll be back in the dock next month.